The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (ML). Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of curriculum learning in reinforcement learning, which involves sequencing tasks or data samples to facilitate learning. This makes it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, since reinforcement learning is often used in control systems, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
